OL,7,FHomelessness in Eastbourne is raised
OL,8,Fin Parliament, as Kit Bradshaw reports
OL,9,Ffrom Westminster
OL,11,FA mother-of-three has spoken of having
OL,12,Fto share a cramped bedroom with her
OL,13,Fchildren, after losing her family home
OL,14,Fin Eastbourne.
OL,16,FKelly Mirza-Clay said the temporary
OL,17,Fcouncil accommodation was "incredibly
OL,18,Fhard" for her family, who were made
OL,19,Fhomeless in July.
